review_title: Well took a plunge and like one reviewer said these came in with not even ...
reviews: Well took a plunge and like one reviewer said these came in with not even close the blend they advertise, it's in fact 74% Polyester/25% Cotton/1% Spandex, will keep them since the price was good but if you are looking for cotton first then look elsewhere.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

reviews:
I received these ankle socks a few days a ago. I'm very please with that product so far.

-First wash went well. The socks did not shrunk much
-It is a nice quality product
-Great price to value ratio
-Socks are not to thick. You will not be bothered when you wear them in a pair of shoes
- I wear 9 US shoe size and they fit well.

Highly recommended.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

review_title: Will fit a ladies larger foot only not a man's large foot!
reviews: OK so I knew what I was purchasing because I had purchased these exact socks twice before at a bargin basement store. So what I have to say is I am a ladies size 9 shoe and these JUST fit my foot with no room for anymore stretch and they shrink even more after washing. So men beware if you have a large foot these will not fit you. For the price they are worth the money and and on a scale of 1-10 (10 being very warm) they are about a 5 on the warmth scale. All-in-all I would recommend If you are a guy and have small size feet then I say go for it but no way if you have large feet. Ladies yes go for it if you are a size 9 or smaller.. Because these were good for me I am giving these a **** star rating but in actuality these should be sold in the ladies section not the mens.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

reviews:
Pros:
- Comfortable
- Fit fairly well with no loose/baggy areas
- Never feel any of the seems on your feet
- Great value
Cons:
- The size range says 6 - 12. I'm about a size 11 and they're a little tighter than I would like
- On the first wear one of them ripped along one of the seems of the heel (due to being a little tight)
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

review_title: Douce et confortable, mais un peu serré à la cheville
reviews: Je les ai acheté pour mon fils de 10 ans et ils sont parfaits pour lui. Par contre, je les ai essayé pour voir si j'en achetais pour moi également et l'élastique à la cheville était trop serré. J'ai des chevilles solides, mais n'ai jamais été aussi serré dans des bas. Conseillé si vous n'avez pas de grosses chevilles. Les chaussettes sont super douces et confortables. J'en rachèterai certainement pour mon fils.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

reviews:
I love these short socks. I ware them over-top of my much more expensive compression socks to help extend their life.
They provide extra cushioning where it is needed in my shoes and and do a great job of extending the life of my compression socks. They are short enough that most people do not notice I'm wearing two pairs of socks.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

reviews: First and foremost, the advertised fabric composition is in fact correct, at the very least the white one is. They don't wick sweat any better than your typical value socks, I walked for about 13,000 steps in them in 20° C, mostly sunny weather conditions and about 4,000 steps in I could already feel the sweat, not horrible but kind of bugging. If you could get them for about $1.50 a pair or less, just grab them, specially the black ones.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

review_title: Pretty hard to go wrong with these socks
reviews: Pretty hard to go wrong with these socks. Soft and they last quite a while. I wear them daily and for things like mountain biking or just around the house when my feet are cold.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

reviews:
Good quality, and comfy. Not sure what else to say. I bought a bunch of packs, and threw away my hodge-podge of mismatched socks I'd been wearing for years.

I really enjoy these. They're soft, they fit well, and I don't hate them (which if you knew me, would realise is saying a lot.)
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

reviews: J'ai acheté ces bas pour mon garçon de 14 ans qui perce toujours ses bas. La grandeur est bonne, mais côté durabilité nous ne somme pas certain qu'ils dureront. Lorsqu'ils sont mis dans le pied, on voit que c'est un peu mince sur le côté. Sinon, le bas est très bien. Bon rapport qualité / prix.
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Sport 6 Pack Ankle Socks

reviews: I wear size 7 men's shoes. My foot is very wide. These fit perfectly. I love that they are low cut, it makes it much easier to wear socks in boots that are low cut like this. Very comfortable and warm socks. Great!

reviews: My favourite sock, so much so that I bought 3 of these and only wear them day to day. Good in the summer, doesn't get super sweaty yet good in the winter to be warm enough! Can't get enough of these socks and will probably continue ordering them as my old ones die off!!
